author: Inside Edition
description: Some of 2025's most incredible stories were nothing short of miracles. In Colorado, a grandmother fell out of her car when her vehicle jackknifed. She was a quarter mile from home without a cell phone and the only thing she could do was crawl. Eventually her son showed up looking for her. In New Jersey, a lifeguard was impaled by a beach umbrella in a freak accident. Doctors had to cut the pole out of Alex Kaus' shoulder. And, brave little Leah Lendel survived a shark attack.
title: Incredible Miracles of 2025

author: Inside Edition
description: 'Tis the season for post-holiday sales. Inside Edition went shopping with Brian Vines from Consumer Reports Magazine. Vines says one of the best things you can do in January is get into stores because after people return things, stores can be overwhelmed with merchandise. Some post-holiday shoppers found great deals on beauty products at the American Dream mall in New Jersey. For holiday accessories, Vines says they are among the most heavily discounted items.
title: Tips On Finding Post-Holiday Sales

author: Inside Edition
description: A violinist is accusing Will Smith of "predatory behavior" and "sexual exploitation" in a lawsuit. Brian Joseph King made a name for himself when he competed on "America's Got Talent" and placed as a top three finalist in 2018. In 2025, King says he was hired to go on tour with Smith and his band. King says after he made allegations of sexual harassment to Smith's management team, he was fired. Smith's attorney fired back calling the allegations "false, baseless and reckless."
title: Violinist Accuses Will Smith Of Sexual Harassment In Lawsuit

author: Inside Edition
description: Dr. Spencer Tepe, a 37-year-old dentist, and his wife Monique were about to celebrate their fifth wedding anniversary when they were murdered in the home where they were married. Their two children, who are both under five, were unharmed. The murder mystery unfolded when Dr. Tepe did not turn up for his practice near Columbus, Ohio and his worried co-workers called 911 to ask for a welfare check. Family friends saw a horrific scene through the window of the house.
title: Investigation Ensues After Dentist And Wife Found Dead In Home

author: Inside Edition
description: A 6-year-old ballerina was wheeled on stage for a special performance of "The Nutcracker" and surrounded by her fellow dancers. Moments later, the other ballerinas backed away to reveal little Morrie Covin standing on her own two feet. Two years ago, doctors were not sure Covin would survive after a freak accident at her grandparents house in Alabama. The young girl and her mother spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall.
title: 6-Year-Old Ballerina Stands For First Time After Freak Accident

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump revealed that he takes four times the daily aspirin dosage that doctors usually recommend. Trump says he takes 325 milligrams of aspirin a day for "cardiac prevention" but he acknowledges his doctors say he should really be taking a baby Aspirin dose, which is 80 milligrams. Many doctors are questioning Trump's aspirin regimen. Inside Edition asked Los Angeles cardiologist Dr. Rigved Tadwalkar for his opinion.
title: President Trump Says He Takes 4 Times Recommended Aspirin Dosage

author: Inside Edition
description: Elleshia Anne Seymour was last seen at an airport with four children, boarding a plane to Europe.
title: Where Is Utah 'Doomsday Mom' #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It's flu season, especially for birds. A sanctuary in Iowa says the disease is wreaking havoc on the avian population. Iowa Bird Rehabilitation says it is trying to contain the outbreak by taking in sick birds, although they admit many of them won't survive. Rescuers tell KCCI that deceased birds can still transmit the disease. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Animal Sanctuary Trying To Get A Grip On Bird Flu Outbreak

author: Inside Edition
description: A frightening car crash near Las Vegas, Nevada saw a driver land in an unexpected place.
title: Car Crash Driver Ejected Into Backyard Pool #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Amy Creel got a call from her husband, telling her she needed to come home immediately. The family had just received an enormous delivery of Amazon packages. Thousands of packages filled their Maryland driveway. So what was in all those boxes? Amy told Inside Edition it was "dog food and treats and toys and beds, anything you can imagine for dogs." Amy is an animal rescuer, and she had asked her community for donations for the holidays.
title: You Won't Believe How Many Amazon Packages This Maryland Family Got
